<TEXT>
the price of the best seats at the royal opera 
house covent garden will rise to about 170 each when luciano 
pavarotti and placido domingo sing there next season general 
director jeremy isaacs says 
we either charge these prices or we go out of business 
isaacs told a news conference wednesday 
he said performance standards at one of the worlds leading opera 
houses need to be improved at a time of falling government subisidy 
next years subsidy is 236 million 40 percent of the royal 
operas income and down from 60 percent five years ago 
isaacs hopes that spanishborn tenor domingo will return in 
january to repeat his title role in giuseppe verdis otello and 
that italian tenor pavarotti will star in gaetano donizettis 
lelisir damore in february 
we expect no falling off at the box office isaacs said 
the director also announced an 11 percent overall rise on seats 
for other than special performances the best seats will be 140 
seats at the very top of the house where only a corner of the stage 
can be seen remain at 4 
