report their output with such detail pedersen said 
in 1987 the united states produced a total of 176 million 
handguns and 101 million rifles including regular bolt and pump 
action armaments as well as semiautomatics pedersen said that was 
a 300000 jump in both categories handguns and rifles from the 
previous year and officials believe the number probably increased 
in 1988 
