<TEXT>
israeli teenagers are playing a form of russian 
roulette that involves dodging speeding cars in an apparent attempt 
to share the dangers faced by israeli soldiers an official said 
thursday 
the game which has swept the country in epidemic form appears 
in different versions nationwide said shai gadish head of the 
education ministrys road safety unit 
teenagers either lie in the path of an approaching car and wait 
until the last moment to scamper away or leave school bags in the 
middle of the road darting out to snatch them from oncoming cars 
gadish said in an interview with the associated press 
the education and transportation ministries have sent 
psychologists to high schools in an attempt to discover why the 
dangerous game is so popular he said 
gadish said teenagers hear about the brave deeds of older 
friends and brothers in the army they want to imitate them by 
exhibiting their own courage by endangering their own lives 
he said 
israelis are drafted into the army on their 18th birthday men 
serve for three years and women for two 
we live in a society where you need to show courage gadish 
said these youths know its dangerous in the streets and that 
they can show their bravery there 
only one youth has been slightly injured playing the game 
transportation ministry officials said 
gadish said teens usually play the game on their way home from 
school and high school principals have asked parents to discourage 
their children from participating 
we are worried that the more publicity this game of russian 
roulette in the streets receives the more popular it will become 
said atniel schneller of the transportation ministry 
</TEXT>
