<TEXT>
auto accident victims with lawyers claim more 
neck and back injuries than those without legal assistance an 
insurance industry study reported thursday in speculating that 
lawyers drive up insurance costs 
the study also said that on average one out of six accident 
victims hiring lawyers was steered to a particular doctor or clinic 
by the lawyer and said that people represented by lawyers hire 
substantially more chiropractors physical therapists and 
psychotherapists 
the findings came from a study of 46694 injury claims paid by 34 
insurance companies in the spring and summer of 1987 
those companies sell nearly 60 percent of us auto insurance 
the claims were made under five coverages bodily injury liability 
uninsured and underinsured motorists personal injury protection and 
medical payment 
states with high attorney involvement tend to have high auto 
injury costs and states with low attorney involvement tend to have 
low auto injury costs said the study conducted by the 
allindustry research advisory council a group of insurance 
industry trade associations and companies 
at the association of trial lawyers of america whose members are 
plaintiff attorneys in personal injury cases spokeswoman madeline 
applebaum said no one had seen the study and she could not comment 
the insurance group found that almost 45 percent of claimants 
hired lawyers up from more than 31 percent in 1977 the group 
speculated that the ending of restrictions on advertising by lawyers 
in 1978 might have helped cause the increase 
the average bodily injury claim payment increased 139 percent in 
those 10 years well ahead of the 85 percent increase in the 
consumer price index 
after noting a 124 percent increase in the cost of medical care 
the study said another possible reason for the large incurease in 
auto injury costs is that attorney involvement has increased 42 
percent since 1977 
</TEXT>
