<TEXT>
the senate refused thursday to dismiss 
impeachment charges that federal district judge alcee l hastings of 
miami conspired to get a 150000 bribe and later lied about it at 
his trial 
the senate voted 921 against dismissal of 15 of the 17 articles 
of impeachment against the 52yearold miami judge the lawmakers 
then voted 930 against dismissal of another article 
hastings had not sought dismissal of still another charge that 
he disclosed information obtained from a federal wiretap and thus 
torpedoed a federal investigation of miamiarea corruption 
the senate acted after 2 hours of deliberation on the 
52yearold judges move for dismissal of the charges on grounds 
that he had been acquitted in a 1983 trial and could not get a fair 
hearing in the senate now in any case because too much time has 
passed 
sen howard metzenbaum dohio voted in favor of dismissal on 
the first of hastings two motions which would have dropped the 
first 15 of the articles of impeachment 
metzenbaum was not reached immediately for comment but press 
secretary nancy coffey said the senator had constitutional qualms 
about an impeachment trial on charges of which hastings already had 
been acquitted 
those were the counts on which he was acquitted and the senator 
had constitutional concerns about double jeopardy coffey said 
the senates decision sets the stage for an impeachment trial 
expected to take as much as six weeks before a special senate 
committee 
the panels proceedings are to be videotaped for viewing by 
senators who lack time to sit through the lengthy presentation of 
evidence the case then will come back to the senate floor for a 
vote on whether to remove hastings from the bench and take away his 
89500 annual salary 
hastings himself on wednesday took the senate floor to make a 
personal appeal to the lawmakers to drop charges that he plotted to 
obtain the payoff and then committed perjury to win his 1983 
acquittal 
i proclaimed my innocence then as i have from the outset and as 
i do now hastings told the lawmakers 
rep john bryant dtexas one of a panel of house prosecutors 
told the senate however that the judges doublejeopardy defense did 
not apply to impeachment trials and that hastings should forfeit his 
job because of his inexcusable breaches of the public trust 
in contrast the senators deliberated behind closed doors on 
thursday and voted on hastings dismissal motion without any public 
debate 
hastings stands accused of conspiring with washington attorney 
william borders in 1981 to reduce from threeyear prison sentences 
