des moines food wholesaler questioned whether officials overreacted 
its just been blown out of proportion loffredo said 
fruits imported from chile include grapes nectarines peaches 
plums apricots pears granny smith apples cherries raspberries 
blueberries cantaloupe and honeydew melons substitute sources are 
available for most types of fruit except for grapes virtually all 
of which come from chile at this time of year 
