the great lakes region needs 9 million to buy 
the only known chemical to kill the sea lamprey and develop other 
means of controlling the parasitic eel or risk devastation of the 
salmon and trout population a new york congressman says 
rep frank horton rny said wednesday that without the 
expenditure the lamprey population could double by the year 2000 
if the lampreys double this will cause the salmon and trout 
populations to be cut in half costing sport and commercial 
fisheries an annual economic loss of 14 billion and some 33600 
jobs in the great lakes basin 
he said the regional great lakes fishery commission based in ann 
arbor mich needs 9 million to keep the lamprey under control 
and the fishery thriving 
lampreys native to the atlantic ocean entered the great lakes 
through the erie canal in the 1880s and decimated the trout 
whitefish and chub populations they attach to fish with their 
sucking mouthpiece and feed on body fluids sometimes killing the 
host 
anyone who has been around long enough can remember a time when 
it seemed every trout and salmon pulled from lake ontario had at 
least one and sometimes more lamprey eels stuck to their side 
horton said the lamprey eel devastated the great lakes fishing 
industry a few years ago but weve come back from it 
the only safe and effective lamprey killer is a chemical tfm 
