if demand for 273 takes off hayman will face some ticklish 
marketing 
prestige products pose salespitch paradoxes people who fancy 
such goods from perfumes to watches to the latest exotic dog breed 
typically dont want things just anybody can buy 
so from a merchandizing standpoint the problem becomes one of 
satisfying demand enough to stimulate interest but not so much that 
the product loses the special cachet that scarcity supplies 
moreover the availability of prestige perfumes is overflowing 
movie stars from elizabeth taylor to cher clothing designers and 
entertainers have added their own contributions to the gushing 
stream of new products 
a footnote to the recent history of numerous perfume 
introductions is the us debut in march of fragrances by bic corp 
of throwaway razor ballpoint pen and cigarette lighter fame 
andrew shore who follows the scent business for shearson lehman 
hutton inc says the lifespan of perfumes is frequently as short as 
12 to 24 months if a fragrance lingers for four years or so it is 
considered a franchise from which successful spinoff products can be 
derived 
incredibly saturated is how shore describes the market 
adding that it is polarized with ultra highpriced items at one 
extreme and mass market stuff at the other 
unit sales have fallen for the past five years he says modest 
growth in sales value occurred because new fragrances fetch 
increasingly higher prices he estimates retail sales rose to 325 
billion in 1988 up from 315 billion a year earlier 
hayman has a simple answer to whether 273 will rise to the top 
theres always a market for the best he said during an 
interview while on one of his frequent trips to new york 
273 is described as a flowery fruity spicy blend of more than 
250 ingredients with the key ones being gardenia tuberose and 
jasmine its components are expensive and so is its packaging 
the crystal pyramidshaped bottle is embossed with a 24 karat 
gold line surrounding the stopper bright yellow reminiscent of the 
giorgio hue and haymans favorite color and fireengine red are 
used for 273 as well as for the beverly hills store 
during a conversation hayman who left his native switzerland 
for the united states in 1941 and speaks swiss french and english 
gives the impression he would rather not know the word discount 
in any language 
his boutique which claims to have the highest sales per square 
foot of any store in the country never marks down prices on 
merchandise for more than 20 years of running the store hayman has 
had the good fortune to discover littleknown designers who 
cultivated big followings such as halston 
the boutique was originally called giorgio by george grant who 
decided to italianize his name because italian imports accounted for 
much of the clothing carried in the shop hayman bought out grant 
and another partner in the mid1960s 
hayman seems to embody beverly hills he owns a vintage rolls 
royce and is definitely a have not a havenot 
recently he appeared fit and pleasantly tanned clad in a 
expensively styled suit recovering from back surgery required after 
years of jogging he was more comfortable standing through an 
hourlong interview in his suite at a chic hotel on the east side of 
manhattans central park 
when his former wife gale came up with the idea that blossomed 
into giorgio perfume hayman was disinterested at first i 
thought it was not a good idea he says he doesnt normally wear 
fragrances himself but now the business is in his blood 
at 63 hayman says he has no intention of retiring anytime soon 
and hopes to establish his clientele privee french for private 
client as a perfume powerhouse 
end adv for sunday march 19 
