<TEXT>
southern catfish farmers long unable to penetrate 
the huge but finicky new england seafood market are finally winning 
over yankees by abandoning the hush puppy approach in favor of 
lemonpepper marinade and recipes like catfish and artichoke au 
gratin 
using a traveling chef to tout nouvelle catfish the nations 
largest processor delta pride catfish inc of indianola miss 
says it has tripled sales in new england during the last six months 
down south its catfish hush puppies cole slaw and french 
fries delta pride president sam hinote said at a recent 
fishindustry trade show in boston but we know that just doesnt 
go up here 
what does go said lisa martel executive chef at rebeccas 
restaurant on beacon hill is catfish in lemoncaper beurre blanc 
weve had it on the menu for four months ms martel said 
at first it wasnt really accepted but now its selling very 
well 
southern farmers searching for an alternative to depressed row 
crops like cotton and soybeans began raising catfish in shallow 
fresh water ponds in the early 1970s 
production has grown at a compound rate of more than 30 percent a 
year from fewer than 5 million pounds in 1970 to more than 295 
million in 1988 us department of agriculture figures show 
in mississippi where 85 percent of the nations catfish are 
raised more than 7000 people now work in the industry retail 
sales in restaurants and supermarkets estimated at about 10 
million in 1970 topped 600 million last year 
almost all of those sales however were in the south and 
midwest although new englanders are the nations largest per capita 
consumers of seafood they have long spurned catfish a fact that 
delta pride conagra inc and other major processors realize they 
must reverse if they are to continue their rapid growth 
people up here still think catfish are the ugly old things that 
huck finn pulled off the bottom of the mississippi said hinote 
if we had the image of say rainbow trout wed be selling 
billions of pounds not millions 
delta prides touring chef john folse is trying to capture that 
clean upscale image with recipes like grilled fillet of catfish 
with dijon mustard catfish and artichoke au gratin and cajun 
catfish with oysters and andouille sausage 
conagras country skillet catfish division meanwhile is 
breaking into the new england market with premarinated packs of 
fish in flavors like cajun lemonpepper and mesquite 
two years ago delta pride a memberowned cooperative of 188 
catfish farmers in mississippi and arkansas sold virtually no fish 
in new england now it sends two tractor trailers a week to the 
boston area delivering about 60000 worth of fish at wholesale 
prices 
conagras catfish division based in isola miss declined to 
provide comparable figures but its northeast sales manager bill 
farr said sales in the sixstate region have doubled in the past 
year and are going up fast 
both companies said they have been helped by publicity about 
diseased flounder and tainted shellfish pulled from boston harbor 
and other polluted new england waters 
the thing about catfish is its raised in well water and fed 
on pellets of soybean and corn meal that are certified free of 
toxins said bill allen jr president of the catfish institute a 
trade association in belzoni miss with all the concern about 
ocean pollution the timing for catfish should be perfect 
for retailers catfish also has two other advantages a steady 
yearround supply and constant prices averaging between 4 and 5 a 
pound at retail outlets in new england said kenneth howe seafood 
sales manager for stop amp shop inc a chain of 115 supermarkets in 
massachusetts rhode island and connecticut 
when stop amp shop first began carrying catfish three years ago 
howe said there was a lot of resistance after heavy 
advertising cooking demonstrations and sales promotions sales 
picked up but they still dont rival traditional favorites like 
cod and haddock 
people like catfish howe said but this is still good old 
new england 
end adv for monday march 20 
