<TEXT>
longstruggling maxicare health plans inc 
filed a federal bankruptcy petition thursday but promised to keep 
serving the 1 million americans covered by its plans in a dozen 
states 
the company which operates health maintenance organizations 
under the names maxicare healthcare usa and healthamerica 
announced it sought protection from creditors under chapter 11 of 
the us bankruptcy code 
maxicare promised to keep serving patients and to continue 
paying doctors and hospitals the filing made in us district 
court in santa ana gives the company a reprieve from creditors and 
allows it to continue operating under court supervision while 
seeking to reorganize 
included in the filing are the los angelesbased parent company 
and operations in alabama arizona california illinois indiana 
louisiana north carolina ohio pennsylvania south carolina texas 
and washington 
excluded is the companys wisconsin hmo 
maxicare once the nations biggest private hmo has been losing 
money for two years and in recent months has cut membership from 
23 million to 1 million by selling several health plans in 14 
states in announcing the bankruptcy peter ratican chairman and 
chief executive officer revealed the company was negotiating sale 
of its california plan previously said to be part of the solid 
core the company intended to retain 
ratican said in a news release the company filed for bankruptcy 
because it couldnt pay its bills 
these actions enable us to protect our operations while gaining 
the time to finalize and implement a plan for reorganization 
ratican said we acted in the face of increasing demands by 
creditors and our inability at this time to obtain additional 
financing 
maxicares stock which sold for as much as 28 a share in the 
companys boom years a decade ago closed at 1875 cents a share 
thursday down 50 cents from wednesdays close 
maxicare saddled with debt hit along with the rest of the hmo 
business with soaring medical costs and struggling to overcome the 
effects of an ambitious expansion drive has logged losses in eight 
straight quarters 
in the first nine months of 1988 the company lost 2505 
million final 1988 results havent been reported 
debt as of december included 150 million in bank loans and 295 
million in bonds 
maxicares health plans are structured in the form of health 
maintenance organizations under which customers generally enrolled 
through their employers are entitled to visit designated doctors 
generally for a small fee 
doctors are paid on a set monthly budget rather than being 
reimbursed for specific services the intent is to cut the overall 
cost of medical care by encouraging people to get regular checkups 
and preventive treatment rather than waiting to seek treatment 
until a medical crisis strikes 
maxicare doesnt own hospitals or clinics as do some hmos so 
its assets consist primarily of a management team and good will 
or its image with customers 
founded in 1973 by the husbandandwife team of chairman fred 
wasserman and president pamela anderson maxicare grew quickly 
capitalizing on the industrys belief that hmos were the wave of the 
future easily raising money through stock sale and loans the 
company grew into a national health plan 
by the mid1980s hmos were under pressure from rising medical 
costs but maxicare bit off a big chunk of new business in 1986 by 
buying two ailing competitors healthcare usa and healthamerica 
the strain of trying to digest the acquisitions was compounded by 
managements inability to keep costs and the number of doctor visits 
down said analyst steven reid who follows the company for the lh 
friend amp co inc investment firm in los angeles 
founder wasserman and ms anderson were ousted in august 1988 and 
replaced with ratican an outside director with a background in the 
entertainment business most recently as president of ailing de 
laurentiis entertainment group inc which now is in chapter 11 
but he has so far been unable to reverse the slide 
reid said ratican by reassuring investors the firm could work 
its way out of the hole has done plan members a disservice 
youve got a situation where a layman has an opportunity to 
switch plans and he reads in the paper this companys in good 
shape he continues his enrollment reid said 
the bankruptcy filing comes at a critical time for the companys 
hopes at resurrection because workers generally are given the 
opportunity to switch medical plans each june reid noted competing 
medical plans already have started marketing themselves among 
employees and the filing is likely to both distract maxicares 
management from that marketing effort 
</TEXT>
